This paper discusses a formal framework for cooperative transmission of data in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also introduces novel indices for measuring the effectiveness of probabilistic and cooperative information transmission, which relates to the sub-category of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the design of machine learning algorithms, which falls under the sub-category of "Information Theory" (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses inductive biases for learners optimized for cooperative inference, which relates to the sub-category of "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the Teaching Dimension in deterministic settings, which falls under the sub-category of "Logic in Computer Science" (cs.LO).
